<p>There were a lot of comments about Project Resurrection (37 mentions), both good and bad.</p>
<p>There was the frequent sentiment for the wiki to return to &quot;how it used to feel&quot; usually accompanying Series III or Horror responses. To which, all I can say is that the site's culture and tastes have evolved since Series I. This is not saying that one was better than the other, just that the tastes have changed.</p>
<p>There was also a lot of worrying about running out of original ideas, and difficulty finding SCPs since the series are so numerous now. I can understand that difficulty and sympathize, since I have some difficulty thinking up original ideas as well. All I can say is that it stretches your creative muscles to find something new. As for finding specific SCPs in the mainlist, you can either use the <a href="/tag-search">Tag Search</a> page (thanks, Crayne!) or use Wikidot's search function at the top of each page. Finally, you can hop into chat (if possible) and see if anyone can help you out. The hivemind is usually pretty good at pulling up specific SCPs.</p>
